<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>English Lessons - Synonyms and Antonyms</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:wght@400;500;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles/lesson.css"/>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles/typography.css">
    <style>
        .example-word {
            font-weight: bold;
            animation: pulse 1s infinite alternate;
        }

        @keyframes pulse {
            from {
                transform: scale(1);
            }
            to {
                transform: scale(1.05);
            }
        }

        .synonym-antonym-pair {
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            padding: 10px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background-color: #f8f8f8;
        }

        .word {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #28a745;
            margin-bottom: 5px;
        }

        .synonyms {
            color: #007bff;
        }

        .antonyms {
            color: #dc3545;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="lesson-card">
        <h2>Lesson 3: Synonyms and Antonyms</h2>
        <p>Learn about words with similar and opposite meanings!</p>
        <button id="start-lesson-btn">Start Lesson</button>
    </div>

    <div id="lesson-content" style="display: none;">
        <div class="lesson-section" id="section-1">
            <h3 class="lesson-heading">What are Synonyms?</h3>
            <p class="lesson-text">Synonyms are words that have the same or nearly the same meaning as another word.</p>
            <div class="example-box">
                <p>Examples:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="example-word">happy</span>, <span class="example-word">joyful</span>, <span class="example-word">content</span></li>
                    <li><span class="example-word">big</span>, <span class="example-word">large</span>, <span class="example-word">huge</span></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <button class="next-btn" data-target="section-2">Next</button>
        </div>

        <div class="lesson-section" id="section-2" style="display: none;">
            <h3 class="lesson-heading">What are Antonyms?</h3>
            <p class="lesson-text">Antonyms are words that have opposite meanings.</p>
            <div class="example-box">
                <p>Examples:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="example-word">hot</span> / <span class="example-word">cold</span></li>
                    <li><span class="example-word">fast</span> / <span class="example-word">slow</span></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <button class="next-btn" data-target="section-3">Next</button>
        </div>

        <div class="lesson-section" id="section-3" style="display: none;">
            <h3 class="lesson-heading">Examples of Synonyms and Antonyms</h3>
            <p class="lesson-text">Here are some more examples to help you understand the concept.</p>
            <div class="synonym-antonym-pair">
                <div class="word">Beautiful</div>
                <div class="synonyms">Synonyms: <span class="example-word">pretty</span>, <span class="example-word">gorgeous</span>, <span class="example-word">stunning</span></div>
                <div class="antonyms">Antonyms: <span class="example-word">ugly</span>, <span class="example-word">unattractive</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="synonym-antonym-pair">
                <div class="word">Brave</div>
                <div class="synonyms">Synonyms: <span class="example-word">courageous</span>, <span class="example-word">fearless</span>, <span class="example-word">bold</span></div>
                <div class="antonyms">Antonyms: <span class="example-word">cowardly</span>, <span class="example-word">timid</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="synonym-antonym-pair">
                <div class="word">Begin</div>
                <div class="synonyms">Synonyms: <span class="example-word">start</span>, <span class="example-word">initiate</span>, <span class="example-word">commence</span></div>
                <div class="antonyms">Antonyms: <span class="example-word">end</span>, <span class="example-word">finish</span>, <span class="example-word">conclude</span></div>
              </div>
            <div class="synonym-antonym-pair">
                <div class="word">Happy</div>
                <div class="synonyms">Synonyms: <span class="example-word">joyful</span>, <span class="example-word">cheerful</span>, <span class="example-word">content</span></div>
                <div class="antonyms">Antonyms: <span class="example-word">sad</span>, <span class="example-word">unhappy</span>, <span class="example-word">miserable</span></div>
            </div>
            <button class="next-btn" data-target="section-4">Next</button>
        </div>

        <div class="lesson-section" id="section-4" style="display: none;">
            <h3 class="lesson-heading">Interactive Quiz</h3>
            <p class="lesson-text">Test your knowledge of synonyms and antonyms!</p>
            <div id="quiz-container">
                <!-- Quiz questions will be added here -->
            </div>
            <button id="submit-quiz-btn">Submit Quiz</button>
            <button id="complete-lesson-btn" data-lesson-id="lesson-4">Complete Lesson</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script src="/javascripts/lesson4.js"></script>
</body>
</html>